    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-09-29</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-11-09T21:35:13Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Small Business Fuel Cost Relief Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow certain commercial farmers, fishermen, and small business owners a temporary two-year business tax credit for excessive fuel cost (i.e., for gasoline, diesel fuel, heating oil, and natural gas. Defines &quot;excessive fuel cost&quot; as the amount currently paid for fuel over the Labor Day 2004 price for such fuel, adjusted for inflation.</p> <p>Allows taxpayers a standard automobile mileage allowance of 60 cents per mile in lieu of the tax credit provided by this Act.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
